definition.value: Habenula is a segment of the epithalamus that has as its parts the lateral and medial habenular nuclei and the habenular commissure.
Pineal body is an unpaired glandular organ subdivision shaped somewhat like a pine cone.  It is attached on the midline near the posterior and habenular commissures of the epithalamus.
Nerve trunk which is continuous with right and left optic nerves and right and left optic tracts.
Nerve trunk which is continuous with the optic chiasm and the lateral geniculate nucleus.

definition.value: Stria medullaris of thalamus is a slender fiber bundle on the dorsal surface of the diencephalon which terminates posteriorly in the habenular nuclei.
